cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.DM

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category as the paper deals with the termination of concurrent processes, which is a logical property. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category as the paper presents algorithms for computing asymptotic bounds on termination time. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses VASS as abstract models of programs. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as VASS are used to model parameterized systems. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with the quantitative properties of cycles in VASS.
